# ANSI escape codes
these arent typical words or characters but commands sent to terminal 
the syntax of ANSI code is :
	\033[argument  letter
	
here \033 is escape sign , and [ divides escape code and argument 
here argument is data 
and letter is a command or can be said as opcode



basic argument and letters 
\033  [  2          J      — clear screen
\033  [  1;1        H      — move cursor to row 1 col 1
\033  [  ?25l       (none) — hide cursor
\033  [  ?25h       (none) — show cursor
\033  [  31m        (none) — red color
\033  [  0          m      — reset color

basic meaning of few letters
H    — move cursor (needs row;col as argument)
J    — clear screen (2 means whole screen)
m    — color/style command


we use \033[2 J            for clear terminal 
\033[row;column H    for moving cursor position


# color table for m letter 
30    black
31    red
32    green
33    yellow
34    blue
35    magenta
36    cyan
37    white
0       reset 
these are for foreground colors 
40-47 are same colors but for background

we use with \033[color m



